rComments: She was an incredible professor. I took her a few years ago and still use the lessons I learned. I recall she said to take folic acid four months before trying to get pregnant and I always tell everyone who is trying to do that. She was an amazing professor and she probably helped make a lot of healthy babies with her advice and knowledge.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Gives good feedback', 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Lectures were so boring since she speaks so monotone and slowly. Test covered the most useless and specific information (ex. the analogy she used in class). Case studies were easy marks, but tests were brutal. Has no office hours and never responds to emails.
Interesting course in general, she's very proffesional and has a lot of experience in the field. Material seem easy and common sense but TAs mark very hard :/

I walked into this class scared about the course, but I have to say this is the best psych course I've taken at UTM. Matejka is an amazing prof who presents the class with material that can't possibly bore anyone. LOVE this course. Tests are fair compared to other psych courses. NOT a bird course but definitely one I would recommend.

The textbook material itself was interesting. It was an independent learning type of course. I wished the instructor replied to emails and had office hours. Tests were okay but sometimes appeared to be out-dated and reused from last year or the year before because they did not reflect present material completely. Still an okay course. I learned.
She's one of the best Psy profs UTM has.

short answers are stuff not on slides and in textbook so need really detailed notes and memorize it really well to ace that portion. M.C are really detailed from textbook. easy class if you work hard. always uses the same test format but will never repeat the same questions.
must know textbook and lectures inside out to ace tests. short answers are predictable cause they will be the ones NOT on slides or in the book so must take DETAILED notes to do well.

The class is okay since she posts slide unlike other PSY210 profs, but the material is dry most of the time. She's good at explaining concepts in a clear way but the TA's mark hard. I did pretty well in the final exam though.

Lectures are clear, but very dry. Tests and exams are weighed weird (most specific concepts are tested and the important things aren't; one word answers weighed the same as explanations). Most of the tests are from lectures. No office hours and rarely on campus for help
I took a seminar course on autism with Professor Matejka. It was the best course I ever took throughout my undergrad as a Psychology Specialist. She was a fascinating lecturer and fair marker.

She has no time for students. No office hours, no extra help. In fact, she will take at least a week to reply to an email and when she does reply there were be several minor grammatical and spelling errors in her response. It will also be a one sentence reply.
m.c are wayy to hard, have to pick best answer confusing choices. short answers have to be detailed to get full marks.

The textbook is great, u will learn a lot from it. The M/C part of the tests are fair but the TAs grade the SA component very hard so you must optimize on the m/c. this is one of those profs who's way too busy for her students.  And Her final is not 75% from the material after the 2nd test like she says, its more like 50%, so know everything!

She is smart, but there are many problems with her course. She is not student oriented, she  provides no extra help, she requests for all matters to be directed to TAs. TAs are not helpful because they don't attend lecture and they do grade very hard. Prof has no office hours. She comes to class, lectures, leaves, so if you need help u wont get it.

Amazing prof! REALLY great at explaining things in class! attendance is MANDATORY bcuz most her questions are from lect so take DETAILED notes. shes really pretty and funny too. Only bad this is she wasnt there for extra help bcuz shes busy with soo much other stuff and the TAs werent that helpful!
